commit_message:
Add support to the services decorator for trove

The services decorator previously didn't have support for trove. While
nothing is using it right now it's conceivable in the future. This
commit adds it to the list.

Change-Id: I5c30da6a19243857adf4f19f77181a2545105c21

commit_message:
Add dependency on Router External Gateway property

FIP has dependecy for RouterGateway resource, but it was deperecated in
favor of Router property. So we should add corrsponding dependency for
FIP resource.

commit_message:
Use only FIP dependencies from graph

This patch contains follow important changes:
 - Fix wrong parameter passsed in graph method.
 - Now we use only FIP dependencies from graph.
 - Tests were fixed according to correct logic. Previously we try to add
   router interface to FIP dependecies, when FIPAssociation was defined
   in template. It was incorrect, because in this case such dependecy
   should be added to FIPAssociation insteaf of FIP resource.

Change-Id: I0ee15b80627783fc2a4c037060629e3c2f364b82
Closes-Bug: #1399713
(cherry picked from commit 64a301c5b2555aa04fb78925ef91321bdfa2e174)

commit_message:
Add support for additional identity events

Keystone has started to emit events for CRUD events on more
resources, specifically: regions, policy, endpoint and service.

Change-Id: I6d5f21474dd8f7694ea28b91544ad93c0b421bf9
Closes-Bug: 1429337

commit_message:
Remove redundant creation timestamp from fernet tokens

This removes the creation timestamp from the token's payload in favor of
extracting the token's creation timestamp from the Fernet token format
itself.

Change-Id: I170a07adc1fe6418dfaf2c78e1b439339f1c14ed
Closes-Bug: 1428717

commit_message:
Namespace updates for _i18n and imageutils & fileutils

The _i18n and imageutils modules only have changes
to move oslo.utils to the oslo_utils namespace and
oslo.i18n to oslo_i18n.  So, I have lumped these
two small changes into this one patch.

Current HEAD in OSLO:
---------------------
commit e589dde0721a0a67e4030813e582afec6e70d042
Date:  Wed Feb 18 03:08:12 2015 +0000
Merge "Have a little fun with release notes"

Changes merged with this patch:
---------------------
_i18n.py
  0cc741a9 - switch to oslo_i18n
imageutils.py
  ac17de97 - Use oslo_utils instead of deprecated oslo.utils
fileutils.py
  ac17de97 - Use oslo_utils instead of deprecated oslo.utils

Change-Id: I749dd8869bbc07d980300e0acbf3903ff7b297cd

commit_message:
Move policy enforcement into REST API layer for v2.1 create backup

This patch moves policy enforcement into REST API layer
for v2.1 create backup extension, and adds unit tests.

Partially implements blueprint v3-api-policy

Change-Id: I79397a37b2d5d307f34a4f02baa1a8d11dc59005

commit_message:
Add documentation for key terms and basic authenticating

When our infra folks have questions about what some concepts
are in Keystone, then it's past due for a glossary and helpful info.

DocImpact

commit_message:
linuxbridge UT: Mock get_interface_by_ip

To avoid querying devices on the system running UT,
which might or might not work.

The regression was introduced by
commit b7a56fd1b44649daa1f768157e68a135b9e01dd1 .

Closes-Bug: #1430098
Change-Id: I2dcdf4b9516e0a90dffee26684fdce7f0ce43cd8

commit_message:
Avoid httpretty 0.8.8 as it can break unittests

A hanging issue was occurring with httpretty 0.8.8 when testing
openstack/python-ironicclient.

    * Blacklist 0.8.8

The underlying issue appears to be tracked in this bug:
    https://github.com/gabrielfalcao/HTTPretty/issues/221

Change-Id: I6b63d4b9966c30d7d1d4d287b156f85f0b78f602

[{'created': '2015-02-11 06:54:51.000000000', 'message': 'Hard delete orphan compute nodes

Orphan compute nodes is soft deleted by compute manager currently. However,
commit https://review.openstack.org/#/c/126372/ adds a new constrain which
prevents resource tracker to insert new compute node record  whose host and
hypervisor_hostname are duplicated with those soft deleted records. So that
Nova compute manager will fails to start, if it attempts to loads a driver
which is used to be loaded on the same host. Need to hard delete those orphan
compute nodes, in order to avoid duplication.

Change-Id: Ic0511a4737c35fa40caad7c10eccbf0008f6312f
Closes-Bug: 1417744
'}]
commit_message:
Hard delete orphan compute nodes

Orphan compute nodes is soft deleted by compute manager currently. However,
commit https://review.openstack.org/#/c/126372/ adds a new constrain which
prevents resource tracker to insert new compute node record  whose host and
hypervisor_hostname are duplicated with those soft deleted records. So that
Nova compute manager will fails to start, if it attempts to loads a driver
which is used to be loaded on the same host. Need to hard delete those orphan
compute nodes, in order to avoid duplication.

Change-Id: Ic0511a4737c35fa40caad7c10eccbf0008f6312f
Closes-Bug: 1417744

commit_message:
Arista L3 Service Plugin decomposition

Moving back-end drivers of Arista L3
Service Plugin from neutron tree to
stackforge networking-arista.

Change-Id: I0b10ce12bc10fb74c905ec11e64be8da12f341f4
Closes-bug: 1428909
Related-blueprint: core-vendor-decomposition

commit_message:
Remove db layer hard-code permission checks for service_delete/service_get

This patches remove the hard-code permission checks for db call
service_delete and service_get.

There are elevated contexts in the code used to call this methods which
aren't removed in this patch. The elevated context will be cleaned up
in last step. This is safe if we forget removing some hard-code
permission.

Partially implements bp v3-api-policy

commit_message:
Immediately schedule net to a DHCP agt by default

Change the DHCP scheduler behavior to avoid deferring
the scheduling of networks to DHCP agents. By default,
now DHCP agents will react to the network creation event
and immediately create a port.

Change-Id: I1c1caed0fdda6b801375a07f9252a9127058a07e

commit_message:
Remove db layer hard-code permission checks for service_update

This patches remove the hard-code permission checks for db call
service_update.

There are elevated contexts in the code used to call those calls
aren't removed in this patch. The elevated context will be cleaned up
in last step. This is safe if we forget removing some hard-code
permission.

Partially implements bp v3-api-policy

Change-Id: Ia70028c129588ea8a764196c7f6260beb936e2e1

commit_message:
Fix NotImplementedError handling in interfaces API

attach_interfaces used format_message() of NotImplementedError for
getting message, but NotImplementedError doesn't contain it then
AttributeError happened. This patch fixes this problem.

Partially implements blueprint v2-on-v3-api

Change-Id: I2153756a88f67820821e66a494b892e3017ad788

Hi Anne / Andreas,

I‘m getting errors for enumerated lists when:

commit_message:
Prefer policy to policy_index

When a policy must be associated with an operation (particularly in a
method/function signature), adopt the convention of using the policy
instance (instead of just the policy_index).

This puts the earnest on the caller to make the decision if it can
safely assume the legacy policy was intended.

 * added StoragePolicyCollection.legacy property to name the legacy Policy-0

On the wire operations will still prefer the policy_index (normally
provided in the X-Backend-Storage-Policy-Index header).  If the called
service can not translate the provided policy index to a valid policy it
should return a client error.

 * object-server will return Bad Request for unknown policy

The DiskFile API now requires ObjectController.get_diskfile to accept
the policy instead of the policy_index.  Implementations of DiskFile
that previously expected the policy_idx keyword parameter will need to
be modified to accept the policy instance.  It is still possible to
ignore policy (e.g.  swift.obj.mem_diskfile), but creating a
swift.obj.diskfile.DiskFile always requires a policy and will raise a
TypeError if called directly with policy=None.

The Auditor will skip audit locations for unknown policies (like the
updater and replicator) to avoid potentially quarantining objects it
doesn't know how how to property audit - it will still log a warning
when it encounters a datadir for an unknown policy - but it will not
attempt to audit locations in that datadir.

Change-Id: I81e9cc8492d642e6df5c822d95a48fe4c96caee1

commit_message:
Split out and refactored more secret tests

This is a continuation of the refactor effort of test resources.
Also removed invalid bit test due to it being an impossible scenario.
This should increase readability and remove a reliance on magic mock.

Change-Id: I60fbc1b1839e44ac648266f0e970ac507dcd523b

commit_message:
Fix create orders functional tests for asynchronous order processing

Two of the order functional tests would fail when barbican was deployed
with a queue due to a race condition. This causes them to loop and poll
for a few seconds to let the order process.

Change-Id: I7e7c059a9ca81172a609ef46deae43447300ebac

commit_message:
Removing networks from offline DHCP agents

This patch adds information on the ability to configure
networks to automatically uncouple from DHCP agents
after the agents are offline, or deactivated.

Change-Id: I2f8ce9e2513345c4d31cfc05176dc5d28541bdab
backport: none
Closes-Bug: #1424661

subject: Add support for basic image conversion
messages:
[{'account_id': 6159, 'date': '2015-03-11 15:34:56.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 136, 'date': '2015-03-11 15:41:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

How would this work for clouds with multiple hypervisors with different formats ? I think we would need, at minimum, some sort of noconvert metadata to allow the user to ask for no conversion.'}, {'account_id': 12000, 'date': '2015-03-11 16:05:10.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

(4 comments)

@Tim, I may have misread this, but doesn't it state that conversion needs to be enabled? Do you mean having a way to prevent conversion for happening upon upload?"}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-03-11 17:03:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Verified+1

Build succeeded (check pipeline).

- gate-glance-specs-docs http://docs-draft.openstack.org/85/163485/1/check/gate-glance-specs-docs/733378d//doc/build/html/ : SUCCESS in 2m 35s
- gate-glance-specs-python27 http://logs.openstack.org/85/163485/1/check/gate-glance-specs-python27/9fe9210/ : SUCCESS in 2m 09s'}, {'account_id': 6159, 'date': '2015-03-11 17:19:57.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

(4 comments)'}, {'account_id': 6159, 'date': '2015-03-11 17:20:17.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 6159, 'date': '2015-03-11 17:23:23.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Hey Tim,

The image conversion is optional and as far as this spec goes, it's enabled in a per deployment basis. Note that this is the first step forward to a more complex conversion workflow. The issue this spec tries to solve is to better acomodate the image into the storage backend.

Hypervisors may convert such images to the format they prefer as they do already in some cases."}, {'account_id': 136, 'date': '2015-03-11 17:27:01.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Thanks. My understanding is that the conversion is optional but the deployer is the one who makes the decision rather than the user uploading the images. Thus, if I have a cloud which has lots of KVM and Hyper-V hypervisors, I can only give one format to convert to.

Docker images would be another case where we would not want the automatic converter running.'}, {'account_id': 12000, 'date': '2015-03-11 17:37:45.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 12000, 'date': '2015-03-11 17:40:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2

@Tim, I agree that this may not be something that all users will want to happen every time. That said, I trust operators will be able to know when to enable this or disable it. It would seem that they should know if their use-case does not fit with the feature, especially since this is a very basic implementation of image conversion.'}, {'account_id': 2537, 'date': '2015-03-11 18:44:43.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Thanks for the feedback Tim,

We need to work on maturing the tasks process in a pipeline mechanism. I think taskflow flows help in that process however, that is not easy for operators to establish out of the box. 

Having said that, the flows still help make the image conversion and even the import process optional to the extent of the will of the deployers. So, depending on the federation of your cloud you would be able to do image conversion as per the needs. 

(Not to be confused with - the concept of Glance's universe being single DC still holds true.)

Hope that helps!"}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-03-11 19:22:57.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified+1

commit_message:
Fix deprecated group for eventlet_server options

Several eventlet_server options were moved from the DEFAULT group
and the old DEFAULT group values are deprecated, but since the
deprecated_group wasn't set the oslo.config code was using the
options' new group as the deprecated group. This caused the
server to report that the new values were deprecated when used.

Change-Id: I98bb59b20e50490bdf054df68b5de055abc3db81
Closes-Bug: 1431088

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-03-09 15:33:36.000000000', 'message': 'Support SSL and trace params in get_credentials

Three additional parameters were added to token client in
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/159267/, which need to be
passed to any instantiation of token client within tempest.

Creating credentials via the get_credentials function,
with fill_in enabled, instantiates an AuthProvider, and
thus a token client, without passing the three new
parameters. Fixing that.

commit_message:
Support SSL and trace params in get_credentials

Three additional parameters were added to token client in
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/159267/, which need to be
passed to any instantiation of token client within tempest.

Creating credentials via the get_credentials function,
with fill_in enabled, instantiates an AuthProvider, and
thus a token client, without passing the three new
parameters. Fixing that.

Closes-bug: #1429878
Change-Id: I9340d02cfa560e3e3e30dd5f9f7fd65da8181755

commit_message:
Fix image/server schema for 'OS-DCF:diskConfig'

When disk_config extension is loaded then, rebuild server and
image show/list detail API's response contain 'OS-DCF:diskConfig' attributes.

This patch fix those schemas for that.

Change-Id: Ic24447d05fa8e5d1f4d44661def179d7a9b995f4

commit_message:
CSCO:Tenants not to access unshared n/w profiles

Ensure that a n1kv tenant who has no access to a network profile
belonging to some other tenant, is not allowed to modify that profile.
Currently, a tenant can create networks on any network profile if he
has the network profile id. For this backport the default value for
the config option is set to False for compatibility reasons.

Conflicts:
        neutron/plugins/cisco/db/n1kv_db_v2.py
        neutron/plugins/cisco/n1kv/n1kv_neutron_plugin.py

Change-Id: I53d767acceaa5e2c08e75e6f18847f659cda8d8b
Closes-Bug: 1365727
(cherry picked from commit f0ea09dffc5bbb69febe399d6b077e5b4657cbc7)

commit_message:
Fixes for test_server_software_config

- Fixes building of self.stack_identifier
- Only check updated_time if the attribute exists.
  This allows latest heat agent code to be tested with
  Juno heat (which doesn't expose updated_time)

Change-Id: I3baa03a7305b95960e0d160a0c666e2a60aa0fa6

commit_message:
Make listing security groups faster

If we have a large number of security groups (more than 1000) with
security group rules (about 100 for each group) listing them
could take rather long time(more than 1 minute).

Adding lazy join to backref to SecurityGroupRule model will make
it faster at list on 15%.

Change-Id: I648a48cdefe0faf75c0c62bd8adffc12547293be
Closes-bug: #1426383
(cherry picked from commit 5917fcff32a51e755b7bb90790cac5afd92556e8)

Fine by me, but security groups are not covered by the Hyper-V CI, meaning it won't post any useful information. Normal security group tempest tests cannot run on Hyper-V, since there is a small issue with Hyper-V. The issue is that it cannot create stateful ICMP rules, meaning it won't respond to pings (unless both ingress and egress rules have been added).

There is a commit on tempest to address this issue, but it's been waiting reviews for a few months already [1]. With this commit, the tests for security groups tests can be enabled in the Hyper-V CI and bugs such as this can be detected much faster.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/117520/"}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2015-03-10 11:01:21.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

(1 comment)

Looking at the patch that introduced enhanced RPC method, it also has a fallback mechanism if self.plugin_rpc.security_group_info_for_devices raises exception. Is it not enough for HyperV case?

Or do you just try to avoid the initial check call and a log warning?'}, {'account_id': 8213, 'date': '2015-03-10 17:01:03.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

No, it is not good enough, since the self.plugin_rpc you refer to is an instance of SecurityGroupServerRpcApi. Also, as the method name points out: _check_enhanced_rpc_is_supported_by_server, it will check if enhanced_rpc is supported by the server, not by the agent itself.

Without this commit, use_enhanced_rpc will be True, and it will then use methods that are not implemented in the Hyper-V SecurityGroups Driver.'}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2015-03-11 13:32:50.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2

(1 comment)

commit_message:
Hyper-V: Fixes security groups issue

After this patch If19be8579ca734a899cdd673c919eee8165aaa0e refactored
securitygroups_rpc, prepare_devices_filter attempts to use methods
unimplemented by the HyperV security groups driver.
For this reason, binding ports fails with NotImplementedError if
security groups are enabled.
Until the HyperV security groups driver reaches parity, the
use_enhanced_rpc property should be set to False on the
HyperVSecurityAgent, falling back to the old behaviour.

(cherry picked from commit 7076d9edee29b852833d934761052efcbc6e8fcf)
Change-Id: I1a7ee2b92367d2d59932b8b39372a055bf19951b
Closes-Bug: #1415523

commit_message:
Basic networking guide structure

Created all files and headings for the new TOC.  This patch
combines files from a number of miscellaneous commits, which
will all be abandoned.

This patch set also adjusts heading markups to match documentation
conventions.  Also fixed niceness errors.

Change-Id: I0e423a5bfcf56d9d190a616fb1d135b121df8bef

commit_message:
Remove the expiration timestamp from Fernet tokens

This removes the expiration timestamp embedded in Fernet tokens in favor
of computing the expiration via creation timestamp + CONF token
lifespan, OR using key rotation to tune the lifespan of Fernet tokens
(or the deployer's combination thereof).

Change-Id: I197e206eee41b0815f43354f1d8d67b2224ede88
Closes-Bug: 1428708

commit_message:
Replace the expiration timestamp in Fernet tokens with a ttl

This removes the expiration timestamp embedded in Fernet tokens in favor
storing a TTL in the token.

Change-Id: I20897dd47fc619fc558d27e0776cf6a868e659ea

commit_message:
Put underscore in-front of alchemist helper

Since this is a internal helper object we should
put a underscore infront of its class name to make
sure this is obvious (the docstring says the same
thing but this will help).

Change-Id: I3aeb6a178c8ceda0c36d5f5bb57bb765260cbd3c

commit_message:
README for L2gw to OVSDB communication alternative

The patch set contains the README file that describes about
other alternative using OpenvSwitch IDL class which the L2
gateway agent could use to communicate with OVSDB server.

Change-Id: I4dbf55fd3a856d8aa31fbfae4f18046f85bdbc6c

Overall looks like it's headed in the right direction, a few comments:

- Ideally, we'd land the common-with-nova objects stuff in oslo first, then rebase this onto that, if we can't do that then at least perhaps we can reference an active oslo review in a FIXME or something so we know the code is planned for later removal

- You appear to have unconditionally claimed Intel copyright on everything, even when it's obviously derived from nova code which has existing copyright claims from other companies. IMHO this is a pitfall of trying to assert any copyright in open-source code, invariably whatever you add is either wrong, or quickly becomes wrong.

- There aren't any tests for the new object code

- The schema->db_api->object duplication is concerning, any ideas how we may handle that long term?"}, {'account_id': 4328, 'date': '2015-01-23 09:52:21.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

commit_message:
Just use the local conf variable

The local conf variable populated by the parent class
already ensures the none/falsey case and sets the conf
to an empty dictionary (as well as checks if its the
expected type and more...); so we should just use that
variable instead of duplicating that work.

Change-Id: I824263d5253d428f6a803f470e29d99de3dbf42c

commit_message:
Make is_admin_available not call for a token

It was only doing this when configured with no tenant isolation and
no accounts file.

Change-Id: I39e461cbb7df58923b26684438a4de52ddeb8187

commit_message:
Truncate encoded instance sys meta to 255 or less

In nova/utils.py function get_system_metadata_from_image converts
image metadata into instance system metadata.  Since Nova's DB
column is limited to 255 characters for system metadata, the image
properties are truncated to 255 characters.  However, the Glance
image may have non-English unicode property values that are longer
than 255 after being encoded to bytes.  We need to truncate the
encoded byte property value to 255 or fewer bytes in order to ensure
the DB insert operation succeeds.  The same encoding and truncation
issue was fixed for the instance fault table under change id
I62fa2830b22e367eb9486d09d3c8818a18ebd20d.  This fix refactors
that code fix into a utility method and uses it to fix both problems.

Change-Id: Ie1051777dd09a2fb91afbadad3728956f83452cf
Closes-Bug: #1425657
Related-Bug: #1389102

commit_message:
Retype in driver should have the correct parameters

A parameter mistach happens to the retype method in driver. This patch
adjusts the parameters according to the calling method in manager.

Change-Id: I7902986b3b7a4666337bf0da3dc04245fc0ea28e
closes-bug: #1430605

commit_message:
[WORKINPROGRESS] Add ceph::calamari

Calamari, the web interface/framework for ceph is now open source.
ceph::calamari will be used to install/configure/manage calamari.

This is a quick draft of the installation based on instructions
made available from calamari and calamari-clients.

This is not finished and is definitely a work in progress put forward
for feedback.
This was tested using Ubuntu 14.04 but should also be Debian/12.04 ready.
This patchset does not yet provide a fully functional setup but does a lot
of the legwork.
Still trying to get the compilation of calamari-clients to work.

Change-Id: I6b6053c78ffe297a69f34286979538df1bd4c334
Closes-bug: #1325286

commit_message:
mysql doesn't understand intersect

get_events currently uses intersect to build results. mysql doesn't
necessarily understand intersect so we change the query to be
equivalent query using exists filter

Change-Id: I0960010a503b8a90b62f150831a1d138ecd396bc
Closes-Bug: #1423713

"as of Python 2.6 'error': e.message})"

commit_message:
Always print info logs from the rest client requests

The info logs make it very easy to parse the requests in tempest log
file. However on gate runs we run tempest with debug so we can see the
full req and resp for ever call. However it makes the log just a mess
of debug statements and difficult to trace through by hand. This commit
adds the info summary messages back even if debug is set so that we can
trace through. There will be a slight duplication of logging, but it is
worth the tradoff.

Change-Id: I5499f231a91342a184d254e95bc72a7480a0ece0
Depends-On: Ia0de957b681cb924a57af98d99a9389ee234ed5b

commit_message:
unicode error in event converter

it's possible that a unicode error be thrown when attempting to
convert notification to event. this patch uses six to handle this
issue.

Closes-Bug: #1421430
Change-Id: Icf450792fd2921344c2a432e5a72be18dda33ac9

Python 2.7.9 doesn't support ssl.PROTOCOL_SSLv3 by default anymore due to
security issues(POODLE attack). We should remove the use of ssl.PROTOCOL_SSLv3
in nova.

The oslo-incubator code changes were already merged in

commit_message:
Fixed ssl.PROTOCOL_SSLv3 not supported by Python 2.7.9

Python 2.7.9 doesn't support ssl.PROTOCOL_SSLv3 by default anymore due to
security issues(POODLE attack). We should remove the use of ssl.PROTOCOL_SSLv3
in nova.

The oslo-incubator code changes were already merged in
I41c6598cb874b79c391f8b4e4607b85c4660bd2f.

Change-Id: I2c7a8483e80eca8b827a9cec4c7699920f806f3c
Closes-Bug: 1395095

commit_message:
Allow specification of ssh_authorized_key.

Pass ssh authorized key to magnum if specified.

Implements part of bp introduce-coreos

Change-Id: Id36e095a488402e63bbdae90b21007e2f5ff7188

commit_message:
Avoid httpretty 0.8.8 as it can break unittests

A hanging issue was occurring with httpretty 0.8.8 when testing
openstack/python-ironicclient.

    * Blacklist 0.8.8

The underlying issue appears to be tracked in this bug:
    https://github.com/gabrielfalcao/HTTPretty/issues/221

Change-Id: I703897317cab01710eeb637c29ae283e05b73bb1

commit_message:
Add skip if for tempest running tempest on tempest commits

This commit adds a skipIf check for running tempest jobs on specific
tempest commits. If the proposed commit is a doc only, or a sample
config only change there is no need to run the tempest tests on the
commit.

Change-Id: I664288625727a19edcba6b19343d4dd9762f86dd

commit_message:
Add non-voting trove tempest job

Add a non-voting job that runs only the database tempest tests
and add it to trove and tempest.  This will replace the existing
full runs of tempest on trove for those projects.

Change-Id: I4df41bfff85ccfc2f61a80df8d2e1bb0ea3c7ff9

commit_message:
Adds pool aware scheduling for HNAS drivers

This commit adds the pool aware feature for HNAS drivers. Now, each service
label in HNAS XML config will be considered as a pool unit. In order to be able
to cast a volume to a service, the admin must create 'volume_type's and each
volume type need to have the 'service_label' with the same tag set in the XML
config, and then the user can create a volume with the desired volume_type.

Implements:  blueprint hds-hnas-pool-aware-sched
Change-Id:  Iddff7ad606b06454458fc53bfc7b812f9815f0e1

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-03-11 18:05:03.000000000', 'message': "Update all Oslo module use

Use graduated libraries where available and update the incubated modules
that remain.

Update imports for libraries that were being used already to avoid the
'oslo' namespace package.

Update config file for creating example configuration files and provide
a new sample file based on the options defined in the libraries.

Note: because of the number of libraries involved there is no real way

commit_message:
Update all Oslo module use

Use graduated libraries where available and update the incubated modules
that remain.

Update imports for libraries that were being used already to avoid the
'oslo' namespace package.

Update config file for creating example configuration files and provide
a new sample file based on the options defined in the libraries.

Note: because of the number of libraries involved there is no real way
to break this change up into smaller pieces. Fortunately, most of the
changes are just to import statements.

Change-Id: Ia0de957b681cb924a57af98d99a9389ee234ed5b

commit_message:
Add option to set swift delete after header

Set the swift delete after header in the zuul swift upload script so
that swift handles log deletion for us. Default to a delete after of 6
months but allow the value to be configurable.

Headers are sent per a post. Posts are done per file-job (or queue
entry). Additionals headers can be set up when building the queue.

Co-Authored-By: Joshua Hesketh <josh@nitrotech.org>
Change-Id: Idd3b4b0c9a6819cda5e9b36ce188a61b558873be

commit_message:
Add README and requirements.txt for VMware plugins

These files were forgotten in the decomposition patch.

Related to Blueprint core-vendor-decomposition

Change-Id: Ibd7bba5a287b455c4fcb8252e13ce277c12d44cb

commit_message:
Update help message for nova boot --file

Stop hard coding the default value for the injected_files quota and just
point to the quota instead.

Change-Id: Ia2abc7e4c3d0e5f954a5c09ff76f11a794e89695

commit_message:
Use get_client when creating ceilometer client instance

The existing rally usage to get the ceilometer Client doesn't
set the SSL verify/insecure params. This fix changes it to use
get_client() to setup SSL params correctly.

Change-Id: I3811573ee9bf2ca6e35c8d363a1149e58fb22e53
Closes-bug: #1430527

commit_message:
Raise QuotaResourceUnknown in the quota engine

This patch lets the quota engine verify whether it manages a resource
for which a limit is being checked.

So far this check has been delegated to the drivers. This is
conceptually wrong and also lead to code duplication.

Unit tests and some docstrings are also fixed accordingly as a
part of this patch.

Closes-Bug: #1430519
Related to blueprint better-quotas

Change-Id: If1467881f13e30afa53a23b904f8eae5c7264834

commit_message:
Make manual checklang target voting

We run this now only when translation files are updated, so a failure
will not block all other changes to merge. Current practice for reviewer
is already to only import if this job passes.

So, mark it voting and add to gate.

Change-Id: Ica791709b0dfbfe00dcac75e3e074f23f94aaeb2

commit_message:
Angular Form Password Validation

A simple form validation to check that password matches.
Required for the angular identity users create and edit action.

Also prevents angular form button from triggering legacy JS events.

Partially Implemenents: blueprint angularize-identity-tables
Change-Id: Ia69f4743b181f051a8574a3e25e626b346ef81b3

commit_message:
Add get_os_admin_context function in context module

A preparation step to get rid of Nova DB usage.

Move a function of OS admin context initialization to context module to
use it in all of API.

We're going to use this function to initialize Nova client to get
instance object with an admin account (which is the only option to get
neccessary extended instance attributes).

Change-Id: I195d899ed245ea3489c7e97b56ee6aaff9a08be2

[{'created': '2015-03-10 17:50:14.000000000', 'message': "Avoid usability regression when generating config

The descriptions of some of the configuration options had been updated
in the sample config, but not in the declaration of the oslo.config
option. This patch maintains parity between the two places these are
currently defined, so that when we switch to only generating the config
files, there isn't a loss of information.

Change-Id: I634c03ac89a0f78cf86992490eb44d2db7a90352
"}]
commit_message:
Avoid usability regression when generating config

The descriptions of some of the configuration options had been updated
in the sample config, but not in the declaration of the oslo.config
option. This patch maintains parity between the two places these are
currently defined, so that when we switch to only generating the config
files, there isn't a loss of information.

Change-Id: I634c03ac89a0f78cf86992490eb44d2db7a90352

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-02-19 22:18:30.000000000', 'message': "Change linux/ip_lib code to better handle address families

The code in linux/ip_lib doesn't handle IP address families
similarly amongst all its APIs.  It also doesn't consistently
handle how it passes options and arguments along to /sbin/ip

So in the spirit of re-factoring, let's try and fix that:

1. Have the code determine the IP address family from its
   arguments, given that it was passed an IP address.

2. Always follow an (options, command, arguments) style.
   Options need a '-' prepended and go first, followed by the
   command, and finally by any arguments.

3. In cases where we can't infer an address family but need
   one it is now required (e.g. listing routes).

I also cleaned-up the IpRule class to fall in line with the
other classes.

Change-Id: Idcb9af698e3ea2d99a6a281c86fa13f51499b628
Closes-Bug: #1419805

commit_message:
Change linux/ip_lib code to better handle address families

The code in linux/ip_lib doesn't handle IP address families
similarly amongst all its APIs.  It also doesn't consistently
handle how it passes options and arguments along to /sbin/ip

So in the spirit of re-factoring, let's try and fix that:

1. Have the code determine the IP address family from its
   arguments, given that it was passed an IP address.

2. Always follow an (options, command, arguments) style.
   Options need a '-' prepended and go first, followed by the
   command, and finally by any arguments.

3. In cases where we can't infer an address family but need
   one it is now required (e.g. listing routes).

I also cleaned-up the IpRule class to fall in line with the
other classes.

Change-Id: Idcb9af698e3ea2d99a6a281c86fa13f51499b628
Closes-Bug: #1419805

commit_message:
Deprecate passing config options via paste file

Log a deprecation warning if there are any options that are supplied to
auth_token middleware via the paste config file. We do this in the paste
specific loaders as other service construct an AuthProtocol object
directly and pass a dictionary that way which we still need to support.

Closes-Bug: #1411068
Change-Id: I1ad9138d04982217b5f1af38257a6c412a7d9c21

commit_message:
Fix missing icon of `Terminate instance`

The icon of `Terminate instance` is `fa-off` had replaced
by `fa-power-off` in current xstatic-font-awesome package
which version is 4.2.0. the other deletion icon is `fa-remove`,
the patch use it as the `Terminate instance` icon.

Closes-Bug: 1425820
Change-Id: I6ad66c97626527aa5ffc1b1a09353685391f9b61

commit_message:
Do not start nova-network service on Ubuntu after package installation

- apt-get on Ubuntu automatically run nova-network service after package
  installation, during this first run nova-network cannot be started
  with customized configuration file it leads to this: it records in
  database with nodes host name (e.g. 'node-2') and even if we start it
  with customized configuration file old record will be in database with
  state 'down'.  All this leads to failed OSTF test: "Check that
  required services are running".

Change-Id: Icc4a7006b409edfe5578ef75549186a50c3e3e89
Closes-bug: 1429085

commit_message:
Makes most of the Swift driver generic

This changeset makes most of the Swift driver generic and
then retargets the existing Swift driver to use it.

Change-Id: I975fa7d2e6fc1cbecd14eeed396da8965d88c937
Implements: blueprint chunked-backup-base-class

commit_message:
Allow LBaaS service provider to be configurable in devstack

Define the NEUTRON_LBAAS_SERVICE_PROVIDER environment variable that
allows the service provider to be defined in the localrc when using
devstack.  Also, use the agent driver as the default.

Change-Id: I8e8ce74eb0847f027209e451d2589db6272ed6d6
Depends-On: Icf34a215e094d27270a5f64df2d1cb995f505370
Depends-On: I51e13a4555e777438af048dd580eacc592435296

(2 comments)'}, {'account_id': 7872, 'date': '2015-03-11 08:06:57.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 13: Code-Review-1

This doesn't solve the issue completely:
If you delete a share network it will disappear immediately. But a tenant router is still blocked since the share service has the state "deleting". What happens if the deletion of the shared service goes wrong? The tenant user can't delete it's own routers and needs an admin to fix it. 

This is also an issue for the resource cleanup in [1].

IMHO the share network need to get a "state" as long it is coupled to the share service. Otherwise it is not transparent to the tenant user.

[1]: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/162628/'}, {'account_id': 8851, 'date': '2015-03-11 08:31:11.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 13:

Mark,

What do you mean by "tenant router" and "share service", moreover "share service" in "deleting" state? Naming "Share service" means process that handles share operations, it is used as "share backend" (based on some share driver).

If you mean that some "share" is in "deleting" state, then in that case entity "share network" won't be able to be deleted. Because it is allowed only when no shares exist with it. See changes to [1]

Sorry, your point is not clear for me.

[1]: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/162138/13/manila/api/v1/share_networks.py'}, {'account_id': 2417, 'date': '2015-03-11 16:48:12.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 13:

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-03-06 13:06:15.000000000', 'message': "Always allow delete share-network when no shares exist

Currently tenants are unable to delete share_networks if there are existing
share_servers. This doesn't make sense, because the share_server exists only
for the share_network, and if the tenant is done with the share_network,
then the share_server can go away safely.

TODO: add/update tests

Change-Id: I8925f3deba64da6b011516163e5554b8134c8c0a

commit_message:
Always allow delete share-network when no shares exist

Currently tenants are unable to delete share_networks if there are existing
share_servers. This doesn't make sense, because the share_server exists only
for the share_network, and if the tenant is done with the share_network,
then the share_server can go away safely.

Change-Id: I8925f3deba64da6b011516163e5554b8134c8c0a
Closes-Bug: #1429123

commit_message:
os.path.exists should be mocked in test case

This commit mocks os.path.exists in the test case
test_start_iscsi_target_fail_wait_daemon in
extensions.iscsi.TestISCSIExtension.  If this isn't
mocked, the file can coincidentally exist on the
environment and can cause failure.

Change-Id: Ibaa8fcae51faaaefc2764411d02621f347d99c03

Split out README into separate files

This makes the docs site a lot more manageable and begins moving us in
the direction of separate user and developer docs.

commit_message:
Handle 404 in os-baremetal-nodes GET

Handle the 404 that python-ironicclient raises so we don't return a 500
